# Windsurf Rules — Gai Framework Source

Gai (`github.com/Hlgxz/gai`) is a Go web framework **library**.

Users use it via: `go install github.com/Hlgxz/gai/cmd/gai@latest && gai new myapp`
`gai new` generates projects with all AI rules pre-configured.

## Framework Development

```bash
go mod tidy && go build ./... && go vet ./...
```

## Core Rules

1. ALWAYS import `github.com/Hlgxz/gai/http` as `ghttp`
2. Handler: `func(c *ghttp.Context)` — c.Success(), c.Error(), c.JSON()
3. ORM generics: `orm.Query[T](db)`, `orm.Get[T](q)`, `orm.Create[T](db, &t)`
4. Models embed `orm.Model` with `gai:"..."` tags
5. Routes: `:param` paths, `Group()`, `Resource()` for CRUD
6. Middleware: return `ghttp.HandlerFunc`, call `c.Next()`
7. Validation: pipe syntax `required|email|min:5`
8. Schema YAML → `gai generate` → Model + Controller + Migration + Routes
9. Files: snake_case.go. Tables: auto plural snake_case
10. No init() outside database/driver/
